1. HbA1c declined by 0.7% in the PCD group.
2. The 95% confidence interval for the HbA1c decline in the PCD group is −0.4 to −1.0%.
3. HbA1c declined by 0.4% in the DSME group.
4. The 95% confidence interval for the HbA1c decline in the DSME group is −0.1 to −0.7%.
5. The decline in HbA1c in the PCD group is statistically significantly greater than in the DSME group.
6. The P-value for the difference in HbA1c decline between the PCD and DSME groups is less than 0.026.
